neighborhood_overview: Brighton is a dissolved municipality and current neighborhood of Boston, Massachusetts,  United States, located in the northwestern corner of the city. It is named after the town of Brighton in the English city of Brighton and Hove. Initially, Brighton was part of Cambridge, and known as "Little Cambridge".  Our area of Brighton is right beside Boston College.
